Hello,

Lots of overlapping windows can get anyone frustrated. One window switch, and your focus is gone. That's why multiple tabs, split view, and keystroke broadcasting are a must for any modern SSH client and terminal. Here's how you can master the skill of handling *multiple tabs* in Termius.

🔌 All your connections are opened in *tabs* by default so that you can focus on the entire terminal. Rename and reorder tabs for easier navigation. Jump to the next tab with Cmd + Shift + ] (Mac) and Alt + ➡ (Win and Linux).

🪟 Use *split view* to see several tabs on one screen for advanced monitoring. Tail logs in one tab while editing config files in another. Arrange terminals for your use case and screen size by dragging tabs on top of each other. Navigate around using Cmd + Option + ➡ or Ctrl + Alt + ➡.

🎨 Customize tabs with different *color themes* to identify tabs at a glance. For instance, using Red Sands will help you avoid mistakes when working with production.

🗣️ *Broadcast keystrokes* to all tabs. Perform maintenance or update configs on multiple similar hosts at once instead of copy-pasting. Enable broadcasting with Cmd + B or Ctrl + Alt + B.

